          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-supporting Si target with thickness of",
                "311 mu-g/cm2"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction products were momentum analyzed",
                "using an Enge split-pole spectrograph."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "DRFTC",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Reaction products were detected at",
                "the focal plane of the magnetic spectrograph by a",
                "position-sensitive ionization drift chamber (PIDC)",
                "filled with 150 torr of isobutane gas, backed by a",
                "plastic scintillator.The PIDC was used to measure",
                "position along the focal plane via front and rear",
                "wires with delay chip readouts, and energy loss in",
                "the drift region dE, via a cathode. Scintillator was",
                "used to determine the residual energy of the particles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction products were momentum analyzed",
                "using an Enge split-pole spectrograph."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Protons emitted from excited states in 27Si",
                "were detected by the Yale lamp-shade array, an array",
                "of five 16-strip silicon detectors arranged in a",
                "lamp-shade configuration.",
                "     Definition of angles",
                "ANG1 - Laboratory angle of split pole Enge",
                "spectrograph, used to detect alpha particles.",
                "The spectrograph was placed at a 3deg angle with",
                "respect to the beam axis to avoid prohibitively large",
                "event rates due to the forward scattered beam at",
                "0 deg to 2 deg.",
                "ANG2-CM - CM angle of proton, detected in Yale",
                "lamp-shade array"
              ]
            }
          ],
